##The base set(good data)
concrete_impute = concrete[(z_slag<=3) & (z_water<=3) & (z_sp<=3) & (z_age<=4)]
y = concrete_impute["slag"]
x = concrete_impute[["cement", "ash", "water","superplastic","coarseagg","fineagg"]]
x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(x, y, test_size = 0.3, random_state = 100)

#creating a linear regression
lin_reg = LinearRegression()
lin_reg.fit(x_train, y_train)
print(lin_reg.score(x_train, y_train))
print(lin_reg.score(x_test, y_test))
impute_x = concrete[z_slag>3]
indice_x = impute_x.index

##The set that needs to be predicted
impute_x = impute_x[["cement", "ash", "water","superplastic","coarseagg","fineagg"]]
pred = lin_reg.predict(impute_x)
print(pred)
i = 0

##Updating it back
for prediction in pred:
    indice = indice_x[i]
    concrete.at[indice, "slag"] = prediction
    i = i + 1
